Unlike the ordinary Bessel functions, which are oscillating as functions of a real argument, "Iα" and "Kα" are exponentially growing and decaying functions, respectively. Like the ordinary Bessel function "Jα", the function "Iα" goes to zero at = 0 for > 0 and is finite at = 0 for = 0. Analogously, "Kα" diverges at  = 0 with the singularity being of logarithmic type.
